---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Shopify Hidden Fees Audit 2026 — Free PDF Download"
  description="Your free copy of the Shopify Hidden Fees Audit 2026. 5 hidden fees Shopify doesn't advertise — and how to eliminate them."
  canonicalUrl="https://shopify-fee-calc.com/shopify-hidden-fees-audit-download/"
  noWebAppSchema={true}
>
  <style is:global>
    @media print {
      header, footer, .no-print { display: none !important; }
      main { padding: 0 !important; max-width: 100% !important; }
      body { background: white !important; color: black !important; }
      .page-break { page-break-after: always; }
      a { color: #2563eb !important; }
    }
  </style>

  <!-- Web view: save/print CTA -->
  <div class="no-print mb-8 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/30 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-700 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-4">
    <div class="flex-1">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200 mb-1">Your free PDF is ready</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-300">Press <strong>Ctrl+P</strong> (or Cmd+P on Mac) → <em>Save as PDF</em> to download this guide. Or read it right here.</p>
    </div>
    <button onclick="window.print()" class="shrink-0 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg transition-colors text-sm">
      Save as PDF
    </button>
  </div>

  <!-- PDF Content -->
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto font-sans">

    <!-- Cover -->
    <div class="page-break text-center py-16 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mb-12">
      <div class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider">Free Guide · 2026 Edition</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 leading-tight">
        Shopify Hidden Fees Audit
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8 max-w-lg mx-auto">
        5 fees Shopify doesn't advertise — and exactly how to eliminate them from your store
      </p>
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        <span>📊</span>
        <span>Average store saves <strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">$3,200–$8,400/year</strong> after this audit</span>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-8 text-xs text-gray-400">shopify-fee-calc.com · Free to share</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Executive Summary -->
    <div class="page-break mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Executive Summary</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Shopify is an excellent platform — but it has a revenue model built on friction. Most store owners focus on their Shopify plan fee ($39–$399/mo) and ignore the five fee categories that quietly drain 3–8% of their gross revenue every month.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">This audit covers each one: what it is, how much it's costing you, and exactly what to do.</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">The 5 Hidden Fees</h3>
        <ol class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xs">1</span>
            <div><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Third-party payment processor fee</strong> — 0.5–2% per transaction on top of your processor's cut</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xs">2</span>
            <div><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Plan upgrade trap</strong> — paying $360 more/year to "save" on fees you don't hit the breakeven for</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xs">3</span>
            <div><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">App subscription creep</strong> — 6–12 apps × $15–50/mo = $90–600/mo in recurring overhead</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xs">4</span>
            <div><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Chargeback cascade</strong> — $15 dispute fee + lost product + lost shipping + processor fee reversal</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xs">5</span>
            <div><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Currency conversion fee</strong> — 1.5% to display prices in multiple currencies (Shopify Markets)</div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Fee 1 -->
    <div class="page-break mb-12">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">1</span>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Third-Party Payment Processor Fee</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 rounded-xl px-5 py-4 mb-6 border border-red-100 dark:border-red-800">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300">Typical annual cost: <strong>$1,200–$12,000+</strong> for stores doing $100K–$1M/yr</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">What it is</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">If you use any payment processor other than Shopify Payments (Stripe, PayPal, Square, Braintree, etc.), Shopify charges an additional fee on every single transaction:</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">Shopify Plan</th>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">Plan Fee</th>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-red-600 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">Extra Fee (3rd party)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800">
              <td class="px-4 py-2 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">Basic</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">$39/mo</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2 text-red-600 font-semibold border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">2.0% per transaction</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800">
              <td class="px-4 py-2 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">Shopify</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">$105/mo</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2 text-red-600 font-semibold border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">1.0% per transaction</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-2 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">Advanced</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">$399/mo</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2 text-red-600 font-semibold border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">0.5% per transaction</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Real cost example</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">A store on Basic doing $200K/year with PayPal pays <strong>$4,000/year</strong> just in Shopify's transaction fee — before PayPal's 3.49% + $0.49 per transaction.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Fix it</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>Switch to <strong>Shopify Payments</strong> as your primary processor — eliminates this fee entirely</li>
        <li>Shopify Payments is available in: US, CA, UK, AU, IE, NZ, DE, FR, ES, IT, NL, BE, SE, DK, SG, HK, JP</li>
        <li>Keep PayPal as a secondary option — Shopify doesn't charge the extra fee on PayPal Express Checkout on Basic/Shopify plans</li>
        <li>Use our <a href="https://shopify-fee-calc.com/payment-processor-compare/" class="text-blue-600">Payment Processor Comparison tool</a> to calculate your exact savings</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <!-- Fee 2 -->
    <div class="page-break mb-12">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">2</span>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">The Plan Upgrade Trap</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 rounded-xl px-5 py-4 mb-6 border border-red-100 dark:border-red-800">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300">Overpayment risk: <strong>$792–$4,320/year</strong> for stores that upgraded prematurely</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">What it is</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Shopify markets higher plans as cost-savers: "Upgrade to Shopify plan to save 0.5% on credit card fees." But there's a breakeven volume below which the upgrade costs you more than it saves.</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Breakeven calculation (using Shopify Payments)</h4>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
          <div>
            <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1">Basic → Shopify upgrade</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Extra plan cost: +$66/mo</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Fee saved: 0.2%/txn</p>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Breakeven: <span class="text-blue-600">$33,000/mo</span></p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1">Shopify → Advanced upgrade</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Extra plan cost: +$294/mo</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Fee saved: 0.1%/txn</p>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Breakeven: <span class="text-blue-600">$294,000/mo</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Fix it</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>Run the <a href="https://shopify-fee-calc.com/shopify-plan-comparison/" class="text-blue-600">Shopify Plan Comparison calculator</a> with your actual monthly volume</li>
        <li>Only upgrade when your monthly revenue exceeds the breakeven threshold above</li>
        <li>Annual billing saves 25% — commit only after you've confirmed the plan is right</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <!-- Fee 3 -->
    <div class="page-break mb-12">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">3</span>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">App Subscription Creep</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 rounded-xl px-5 py-4 mb-6 border border-red-100 dark:border-red-800">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300">Typical annual overspend: <strong>$1,080–$7,200/year</strong> on unused or duplicated apps</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">What it is</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">The average Shopify store has 6–12 active apps. Many were installed for a specific campaign or feature, then forgotten. Others overlap in functionality. Shopify's app billing is "set and forget" — charges keep hitting your card invisibly.</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Common app cost categories</h4>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Email marketing (Klaviyo, Omnisend)</span><span class="font-semibold">$20–$300/mo</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Reviews (Okendo, Yotpo)</span><span class="font-semibold">$19–$119/mo</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Loyalty programs (Smile.io)</span><span class="font-semibold">$49–$199/mo</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Live chat / support (Gorgias, Tidio)</span><span class="font-semibold">$10–$60/mo</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Upsell / cross-sell (ReConvert)</span><span class="font-semibold">$15–$59/mo</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-600 pt-2"><span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Typical total</span><span class="font-bold text-red-600">$113–$737/mo</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Fix it</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>Audit every app in your Shopify Admin → Apps. Log: name, monthly cost, last used, what it does</li>
        <li>Cancel anything unused for 30+ days</li>
        <li>Look for duplication (e.g., two email tools, two review apps)</li>
        <li>Use our <a href="https://shopify-fee-calc.com/app-stack-cost-auditor/" class="text-blue-600">App Stack Cost Auditor</a> to benchmark your app spend vs your revenue tier</li>
        <li>Shopify native features often replace apps for free: basic email (Shopify Email), basic loyalty (Shop Cash), basic reviews (Product Reviews app)</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <!-- Fee 4 -->
    <div class="page-break mb-12">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">4</span>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Chargeback Cascade</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 rounded-xl px-5 py-4 mb-6 border border-red-100 dark:border-red-800">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300">True cost per chargeback: <strong>$60–$200+</strong> (most stores only see the $15 dispute fee)</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">What it is</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">A chargeback isn't just a lost sale. It triggers a cascade of costs that most stores don't track:</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Full cost of one $75 chargeback</h4>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Product cost (COGS)</span><span>–$30</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Shipping cost (outbound)</span><span>–$8</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Shopify dispute fee</span><span>–$15</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Payment processor fee (non-refunded)</span><span>–$2.20</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Staff time to respond (30 min @ $20/hr)</span><span>–$10</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Revenue lost</span><span>–$75</span></div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-600 pt-2 font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white"><span>Total damage</span><span class="text-red-600">–$140.20</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">A chargeback rate of just 0.5% on $500K/year = ~33 chargebacks = <strong>$4,600+ in true losses</strong>.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Fix it</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>Enable fraud analysis in Shopify Payments — cancel high-risk orders automatically</li>
        <li>Use clear shipping timeframes + tracking on every order (most chargebacks are "item not received")</li>
        <li>Send proactive shipping delay notifications (reduces WISMO chargebacks by ~40%)</li>
        <li>Respond to every dispute with documentation: order confirmation, tracking, delivery proof</li>
        <li>Consider Signifyd or NoFraud if chargebacks exceed 0.3% of transactions</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <!-- Fee 5 -->
    <div class="page-break mb-12">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">5</span>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Currency Conversion Fee</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 rounded-xl px-5 py-4 mb-6 border border-red-100 dark:border-red-800">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300">Annual cost: <strong>1.5% of all international sales revenue</strong></p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">What it is</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">If you sell to customers in other countries and use Shopify Markets to display local currency prices, Shopify charges a 1.5% currency conversion fee on every international transaction. This is separate from your Shopify Payments processing fee.</p>

      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">A store doing $100K in international sales pays <strong>$1,500/year</strong> just in conversion fees — silently, in your Shopify billing.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Fix it</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>Evaluate whether multi-currency is driving enough conversion lift to justify the 1.5% fee</li>
        <li>For stores where international is <20% of revenue, consider showing USD-only pricing — many international buyers are comfortable with it</li>
        <li>Shopify Plus eliminates the currency conversion fee — worth it at $500K+/year in international sales</li>
        <li>Consider separate regional storefronts (e.g., a UK subdomain) if international is a major revenue driver</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <!-- Action Checklist -->
    <div class="page-break mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Action Checklist</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Use this 30-minute audit to find hidden fees in your store. Check each item off as you review it.</p>

      <div class="space-y-3">
        {[
          { fee: 'Fee #1', action: 'Check Admin → Settings → Payments. Are you using a third-party processor? Calculate your annual cost using the transaction fee % × annual revenue.' },
          { fee: 'Fee #1', action: 'If your country supports Shopify Payments, switch to it and eliminate the transaction fee entirely.' },
          { fee: 'Fee #2', action: 'Look up your current monthly revenue. Run the Plan Comparison calculator to verify you\'re on the right plan.' },
          { fee: 'Fee #2', action: 'If you\'re on annual billing, note your renewal date and plan to recalculate before renewing.' },
          { fee: 'Fee #3', action: 'List every installed app and its monthly cost. Flag anything unused for 30+ days.' },
          { fee: 'Fee #3', action: 'Cancel at least 2 unused apps in the next 7 days. Set a monthly app review reminder.' },
          { fee: 'Fee #4', action: 'Check your chargeback rate in Shopify Payments dashboard. Flag if >0.3%.' },
          { fee: 'Fee #4', action: 'Review your fraud filter settings. Enable auto-cancel for high-risk score orders.' },
          { fee: 'Fee #5', action: 'Check what % of your revenue comes from international customers (Analytics → Customers by country).' },
          { fee: 'Fee #5', action: 'If <20% international, consider whether multi-currency is justified vs. 1.5% fee.' },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-5 h-5 border-2 border-gray-400 rounded mt-0.5"></div>
            <div class="text-sm">
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-600 uppercase mr-2">{item.fee}</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">{item.action}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="mb-12 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Run the Numbers on Your Store</h2>
      <p class="text-blue-100 mb-6">Use our free calculators to quantify exactly how much each of these fees is costing you — and see your true profit margin.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 max-w-lg mx-auto">
        <a href="https://shopify-fee-calc.com/shopify-hidden-fees-audit/" class="bg-white text-blue-700 font-semibold px-4 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors text-sm">
          Hidden Fees Audit Calculator →
        </a>
        <a href="https://shopify-fee-calc.com/shopify-profit-calculator/" class="bg-white text-blue-700 font-semibold px-4 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors text-sm">
          Shopify Profit Calculator →
        </a>
        <a href="https://shopify-fee-calc.com/shopify-plan-comparison/" class="bg-white text-blue-700 font-semibold px-4 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors text-sm">
          Plan Comparison Tool →
        </a>
        <a href="https://shopify-fee-calc.com/app-stack-cost-auditor/" class="bg-white text-blue-700 font-semibold px-4 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors text-sm">
          App Stack Cost Auditor →
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-blue-200 text-xs mt-6">shopify-fee-calc.com — all calculators are free, no account required</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</Base>
